        @Since(value="7.0")
public Volume(Long volumeID,
                 String name,
                 Long accountID,
                 String createTime,
                 String status,
                 String access,
                 Boolean enable512e,
                 String iqn,
                 String scsiEUIDeviceID,

                 QoSResult qos,

                 VolumePair[] volumePairs,
                 Optional<String> deleteTime,
                 Optional<String> purgeTime,
                 Long sliceCount,
                 Long totalSize,
                 String virtualVolumeID,
                 Map<String,Object> attributes)
        Volumes Info is an object containing information about a volume. The return objects only include "configured" information about the volume and not runtime or usage information. Information about paired volumes will also be returned.
        Parameters:
        volumeID - [required] Unique VolumeID for the volume.
        name - [required] Name of the volume as provided at creation time.
        accountID - [required] Unique AccountID for the account.
        createTime - [required] UTC formatted time the volume was created.
        status - [required] Current status of the volume
        access - [required] Access allowed for the volume
        enable512e - [required] If "true", the volume provides 512 byte sector emulation.
        iqn - [required] Volume iSCSI Qualified Name.
        scsiEUIDeviceID - [required] Globally unique SCSI device identifier for the volume in EUI-64 based 16-byte format.
        scsiNAADeviceID - [required] Globally unique SCSI device identifier for the volume in NAA IEEE Registered Extended format.
        qos - [required] Quality of service settings for this volume.
        volumeAccessGroups - [required] List of volume access groups to which a volume belongs.
        volumePairs - [required] Information about a paired volume.
        deleteTime - (optional) The time this volume was deleted.
        purgeTime - (optional) The time this volume will be purged from the system.
        sliceCount - [required] The number of slices backing this volume.
        totalSize - [required] Total size of this volume in bytes.
        virtualVolumeID - [required] Virtual volume ID this volume backs.
        attributes - [required] List of Name/Value pairs in JSON object format.
        Since:
        7.0

        Volumes Info is an object containing information about a volume. The return objects only include "configured" information about the volume and not runtime or usage information. Information about paired volumes will also be returned.
        Parameters:
        volumeID - [required] Unique VolumeID for the volume.
        name - [required] Name of the volume as provided at creation time.
        accountID - [required] Unique AccountID for the account.
        createTime - [required] UTC formatted time the volume was created.
        status - [required] Current status of the volume
        access - [required] Access allowed for the volume
        enable512e - [required] If "true", the volume provides 512 byte sector emulation.
        iqn - [required] Volume iSCSI Qualified Name.
        scsiEUIDeviceID - [required] Globally unique SCSI device identifier for the volume in EUI-64 based 16-byte format.
        scsiNAADeviceID - [required] Globally unique SCSI device identifier for the volume in NAA IEEE Registered Extended format.
        qos - [required] Quality of service settings for this volume.
        volumeAccessGroups - [required] List of volume access groups to which a volume belongs.
        volumePairs - [required] Information about a paired volume.
        deleteTime - (optional) The time this volume was deleted.
        purgeTime - (optional) The time this volume will be purged from the system.
        sliceCount - [required] The number of slices backing this volume.
        totalSize - [required] Total size of this volume in bytes.
        blockSize - [required] Size of the blocks on the volume.
        virtualVolumeID - [required] Virtual volume ID this volume backs.
        attributes - [required] List of Name/Value pairs in JSON object format.
        Since:
        8.0

      • getAccess

        public String getAccess()
        Access allowed for the volume
        readOnly: Only read operations are allowed.
        readWrite: Reads and writes are allowed.
        locked: No reads or writes are allowed.
        replicationTarget: Designated as a target volume in a replicated volume pair.
